Test of whether kinetic constants can be obtained with BioMark

Copyright (C) 2020 Martin Engqvist Lab

Experiment

..

Experimental data collected on 160719 (DDMMYY) in Petter Wolls group at Karolinska using a BioMark instrument.

Assay conditions, oxidases:

20mM HEPES, pH 7.4

50uM Amplex Red

0,1U/ml HRP

0,1uM fluorescein

0,01mg/ml BSA

0,01% Triton-X-100 and Tween20

# combine data

These look quite horrible. That is because the fluorescecne of the no enzyme control increases with time combined with the fact that some samples maxed out the instrument in terms of intensity, so when normalizing one gets this devreasing slope. This should be fine, however, as we will only use initial rates for the best enzyme concentration, so the sagging part of the lines will not be analyzed.
